## SSE Streaming

### Protocol

The backend `/api/chat/stream` endpoint sends:

```
data: <partial token>\n\n
event: done\ndata: {}\n\n
event: error\ndata: {"detail": "<message>"}\n\n
```

### Hook: `useSSEChat`

Manage all SSE state in the `useSSEChat` custom hook. Do not open `EventSource` directly in components.

```typescript
// hooks/useSSEChat.ts
export function useSSEChat(userId: string) {
  const [messages, setMessages] = useState<Message[]>([]);
  const [isStreaming, setIsStreaming] = useState(false);
  const esRef = useRef<EventSource | null>(null);

  const sendMessage = (text: string) => {
    // 1. Append human message to state
    // 2. Open EventSource to /api/chat/stream
    // 3. On message event: accumulate tokens into streaming AI bubble
    // 4. On event:done: mark isStreaming=false, close EventSource
    // 5. On event:error: show error, close EventSource
  };

  useEffect(() => {
    return () => esRef.current?.close(); // cleanup on unmount
  }, []);

  return { messages, isStreaming, sendMessage };
}
```

### Rules

- Always close the `EventSource` on component unmount.
- Never open more than one `EventSource` at a time — close the previous one before opening a new one.
- The streaming AI bubble is identified in state with `isStreaming: true`; flip to `false` on `event: done`.

